exec-sandbox Firecracker Tier-3 guest kernel — provenance (ADR 010 A1.Q1)
==========================================================================

This records the pinned upstream provenance of the vendored guest kernel artifact. The pin (the
vendored vmlinux + its sha256) is the supply-chain control: dep-scan does not cover a kernel image,
so the artifact is verified by a stdlib crypto/sha256 loader before boot and fails fast on mismatch
(no boot from an unverified artifact). The artifact is also a plain file scannable by code-scanner.

Kernel
------
  Artifact:       vmlinux-6.1.176  (uncompressed x86_64 ELF; built `make vmlinux`, NOT bzImage)
  Linux line:     6.1  (the newest line published in Firecracker's resources/guest_configs/ at
                  build time — floor per ADR 010 A1.Q1; 6.1 is also Firecracker's current x86_64
                  reference line)
  Linux git tag:  v6.1.176
  Linux commit:   fdb6fcb41cc741ad5eaa7995f278dfcb94fdf795
  Source:         https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/stable/linux.git
  sha256:         see vmlinux.sha256 (sibling file)

Kernel config
-------------
  Config file:    microvm-kernel-ci-x86_64-6.1.config (copied verbatim from upstream Firecracker)
  From repo:      https://github.com/firecracker-microvm/firecracker
  Firecracker commit: 5ae6752ed16093bcc3d16eac077d580925422f55
  Applied with:   `cp microvm-kernel-ci-x86_64-6.1.config .config && make olddefconfig`
                  (vsock + virtio-blk + ext4 are built-in: CONFIG_VIRTIO_VSOCKETS=y,
                  CONFIG_VIRTIO_BLK=y, CONFIG_EXT4_FS=y)

Reproduce
---------
  git clone --depth 1 --branch v6.1.176 \
      https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/stable/linux.git linux
  cd linux
  cp <this-dir>/microvm-kernel-ci-x86_64-6.1.config .config
  make olddefconfig
  make -j"$(nproc)" vmlinux
  # the produced vmlinux matches vmlinux-6.1.176 (modulo non-deterministic BuildID/timestamps;
  # the pin is the sha256 of THIS vendored artifact, which the loader verifies).

Note on EOL
-----------
  Linux 6.1 upstream support ends 2026-09-02. When 6.1's successor is published in Firecracker's
  resources/guest_configs/, re-run the build against the newer line and re-pin (bump vmlinux-<ver>,
  vmlinux.sha256, the config, and this note). Until then 6.1.176 is the newest non-EOL point release
  of the newest Firecracker-published line.
